</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graalthedorf>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 6:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: need more info........</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Do you think I'm really that much less likely to die than you? If you're at risk of dropping, you at least have the chance to throw yourself a heal in a pinch or stun the mob for a few vital seconds. You might even have to blow LoH. I can fire off defensive, if I haven't fired it off in the last 10 minutes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In some situations yes. Those abilities you mentioned are great, and I am not going to say they aren't. Their utility is much reduced when tanking a mob unslowed. I can't LoH if I'm stunned. It is very difficult cast a spell if I'm getting hit twice a second. My ability to heal myself is great when you are looking at long term mana efficiency. My ability to heal myself is not so great when in a situation where the difference in tanking ability of a knight and a warrior are most pronounced. I have a very efficient heal that heals 700 points of damage for 225 mana. The downside is it only heals 175 hp a tick. I do have a nice, fast heal that will heal 850 hp in 1 second. The problem is that even that thing gets interrupted quite frequently when tanking an unslowed mob (it also costs 400 mana, which isn't relevant to this discussion) and it has a 5 second recast, so I can't chain it. I can't begin to tell you how many times I've died to unslowed mobs with my lay hands button ungreyed and plenty of mana because I was stunned. By the time I realise that the cleric isn't going to be able to heal me in time and I decide to handle it myself, I usually have 2 or 3 seconds at most to get a heal off. Burning 400 mana every time I get a bit low on hp is a great a way to piss away mana and piss off the cleric, who now thinks you don't trust them. It is also completely unfeasible to do on a continous basis unless the group wants to stop and wait for me to med every other mob. That heal is 400 mana for a reason, it is designed as an emergency heal, on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>someone else</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
If the group is in a situation where we are getting tons of adds that the chanter is able to lock down but the cleric is slowly running out of mana, then those abilities kick large quantities of ass. They do have their strengths and weaknesses though. Those secondary abilites are even better when used by a secondary/ghetto crowd control tank. <br>
<br>
Anything that a warrior will have a hard time tanking will be much harder for a paladin/SK of the same level of gear to tank in the same situation, assuming the primary healing comes from CH. If it is simply a question of healing efficiency then it is a different story. Survival is usually a question of healing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>speed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Will the heal land in time? Will it be for enough hp to buy enough time for the next heal to land? The difference in hp between a warrior and knight can be the difference in whether there is enough time for CH to land. That generally is not the case for most xp mobs...that I can tank. I can't tank giants in PoS. How do I know this? Because no group I've been in has been willing to try. &quot;We need a warrior&quot;. Whether that is the truth or not, I have no idea.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Crusader of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaticfringesk>lunaticfringesk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 6:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ~</span><hr size=1> The more and more I read this, the more Im convinced that this is shaping up like a court of law.  The plantiff and defendant blow things so far out of proportion in their favor that the truth probably lies somewhere in the middle.<br>
<br>
Granted, while I may be seen as just another one of these people that will spew forth non-sense, I can tell you that I honestly dont care if they gave warriors more agro control or not.  Why do I say this?  Well, Im trying to add a *3rd party* point of view, despite the fact that many will immediately conclude that I am biased.<br>
<br>
My main is a 65 SK and I bot a 65 shaman.  That is the main reason that I am replying to this thread, as I can speak from two points of view.<br>
<br>
There were quite a few things I wanted to comment on, so I apologize if this seems a bit out-of-whack order-wise.<br>
<br>
Firstly, while I cant speak intelligently about paladins (&quot;PLD&quot;), I can assure you that SKs SELDOM run OOM, especially at higher levels.  And we dont need C3 (or greater) to get to that point (crack is SO easy to get nowadays though...).  Deathly Tempation is adequate mana regen for me to go for hours on end, to say nothing about Pact of Hate, which actually has a higher mana regen then C3 (C3 is MUCH better overall though).  Sorry, but If you are running OOM, you are not casting your spells wisely.  <br>
<br>
While PoP has gone a long way to *define* the roles of the knight classes, our DPS/heal spells are still awful in comparison to other classes of similar level.  Translation?  Yeah, they help and are really cool to have, but our primary job as a tank (all of us, warriors, SKs and PLDs alike) is to ABSORB damage, not deal damage.  You want to be damage dealer, you have picked the wrong class Im sorry to say.<br>
<br>
The main problem I have with the *warrior* arguement, however, is that many of you have blown it so far out of proportion, it isnt even funny.  A warrior is, in absolutely no regard, a *liability* in a group.  Talk about silly, Im sorry--that takes the cake.  I know of no person that seriously thinks that way at all.<br>
<br>
If I understand this thread correctly, the primary concern from the warriors seems to be *ponging* the mob.  This pong seems to be at its greatest concern when the mob is pre-slowed.  I dont know how many mobs Ive slowed (its a lot though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but you guys are just focused too much on something that doesnt seem that big a deal to me.<br>
<br>
Firstly, malo then slow is seldom resisted in a normal XP environment (PoTactics and above are harder, I admit, but still).  My experience has been slow lands at a very high rate of success in zones such as CoD, PoV, PoS, BoT, HoH, etc..  Why is this important?  Well, a shaman/chanter slowed mob is essentially a turd.  I know that if all incoming mobs get slowed, we have a extremely good chance at winning.  <br>
<br>
For instance, in a 5 person group in PoV, with 1 tank (me) and no chanter, several months ago, we got 5 adds, 2 at the beginning and 3 later on as we were fighting.  All of them got slowed and we only lost one member.  One of the most enjoyable EQ moments I have had I must say.  hehe  Anyways, this is not an effort to say how great we were, but a comment as to the power of slow.  I pretty much believe that a slowed mob (full effect--I hate the ones that have partial) equals a victory substantially all the time.  As a matter of fact, I fail to recall any wipes to slowed mobs.  Its the unslowed adds or somethign that cause all the problems.<br>
<br>
Why mention all of that?  Well, who really cares if you pong a slowed mob?  They are such turds, a wizard could probably tank them!!!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Furthermore, getting agro back is seldom a huge time-sink.<br>
<br>
So, that seems to leave us with an unslowed mob pong.  Well, as stated above, I just dont see that happen all that often.  An unslowed mob pong, however, can cause problems, but the few times that it does happen, it just doesnt seem to present a task that a good to great group cnat overcome.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, however, that yes, I do end up tanking for the majority of my groups.  So, many might immediately jump on the *you dont understand* bandwagon.  Well, actually, I do.<br>
<br>
I frequently group with a 65 warrior friend.  I let him tank over me because....actually, Im not sure why I do, but....hehe<br>
<br>
Anyways, I found myself ponging the mob frequently to my shaman, as I am used to the agro control of my SK, but it was never a big deal at all!  The mob was slowed almost all the time and the warrior got agro back really fast.  It honestly wasnt that big a deal.<br>
<br>
Also, all I had to do was slow the *slow* spell just a little bit and the problem was reduced significantly (although its wasnt too big a deal in the first place--unless you consider that the 3 melee class had to move a little  =P  ).  Malo doesnt seem to make the mobs too mad at all.<br>
<br>
I also bot a 65 chanter friend quite a bit too.  Chanters are FAR MORE TRICKY to control agro, especially when grouping with a warrior.  Tash gets hell-a agro fast, but sure as heck casts fast too. <br>
<br>
However, it still wasnt that big of a deal!  So I have to cast malo/slow (or tash/slow) a little slower.  Big deal.  And did I mention that I am a very average shaman / chanter?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Come on guys, if I can do this pretty well, I cant believe that, for the most part, the shaman / chanter population cant do it significantly better!!<br>
<br>
I guess I just dont see it as that big an issue.  Could warriors use a boost to their agro control?  I dunno---guess so.  But in the big picture, that seems to be a simple wisk of paint to me.<br>
<br>
On a related note, however, one of the few, but primary reasons that SK/PLD are deemed worthy of playing MT in a group is due to their agro control.  If VI was to allow warriors to get and control agro ON THE SAME BASIS as SK/PLD, then YES, without a shadow of a doubt, you would automatically reduce the appeal of grouping with SK/PLD.  I know that some warriors agree with that school of thought and I just wanted to re-enforce that.  There might be an arguement to increase warrior taunt, but it CANNOT ever equal a SK/PLD, all things equal, or you will essentially kill the hybrid tanks.<br>
<br>
Make no mistake about it, agro control is one of the best attributes of SK/PLD at the moment.<br>
<br>
Luna <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eoden01>Eoden01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 7:29 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.xtra.co.nz/hosts/vicky/eq/eodenpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ~</span><hr size=1> I don't feel warriors are asking to taunt like a knight, just taunt better.<br>
<br>
At the moment Knights tank/mitigate arguably 80-90% as well as a warrior and warriors taunt 40-50% as well as a knight.<br>
<br>
For playing my warrior in XP groups I would appreciate either a small upgrade in taunt or a small upgrade in mitigation so that either the gap in agro control between myself and a similarly geared knight becomes smaller, or I have a sightly larger mitigation advantage.<br>
<br>
Ofcourse Im not expecting either so Im just gonna take the groups that come my way and play my chanter when I can't find them.  <br>
<br>
I still enjoy playing my warrior and when I tank I do a good job of it, but its certainly not unusual for me to be in groups where I bag my red blade for my blue blade and let a knight tank because agro control at the touch of a button makes things easier for everyone. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=50585" target="top">Eoden</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Half Elven Warlord<br>
