<br>
You sound essentially honest so I'll take what you say at face value.  You even admit you don't know why you let your Warrior friend tank, I suspect you're just being kind to him.  And there is the crux of the matter.  You have a choice between an SK and a Warrior, and you can't see any particular reason to use the Warrior.  I'm not saying the Warrior should always be the first choice, but damn it would be nice to really be able to say there was a real reason they might be preferable, wouldn't you think?  That is, if you're not doing hard hitting PoS giants and such.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anyways, I found myself ponging the mob frequently to my shaman, as I am used to the agro control of my SK, but it was never a big deal at all! The mob was slowed almost all the time and the warrior got agro back really fast. It honestly wasnt that big a deal.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Maybe for you it wasn't.  You compensated for the difference between your SK and your Warrior friend and went merrily along.  Some people can't do that.  They're aggro understanding deficient.  Some would say stupid.  I would say they just don't understand aggro.  Some people can compensate, but don't want to be bothered.  They know they can keep the SK or Paladin standing with only minor additional healing effort, in most cases, and would much rather have the addtional aggro control.  Which leaves Warriors grouping with people like you, willing to deal with the reduced aggro control of the Warrior, because they don't see it as a big deal. But of course, since you'll take any tank that comes along, if a Paladin or Shadow Knight shows up first, you swoop them up, meaning that the Warrior can be left with just the people that can't adjust or don't want to.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>On a related note, however, one of the few, but primary reasons that SK/PLD are deemed worthy of playing MT in a group is due to their agro control. If VI was to allow warriors to get and control agro ON THE SAME BASIS as SK/PLD, then YES, without a shadow of a doubt, you would automatically reduce the appeal of grouping with SK/PLD. I know that some warriors agree with that school of thought and I just wanted to re-enforce that. There might be an arguement to increase warrior taunt, but it CANNOT ever equal a SK/PLD, all things equal, or you will essentially kill the hybrid tanks.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Understood.  Completely equal aggro control would be bad for the hybrids.  So the point would be to give enough to make slows not a big deal for everyone, then allow the natural difference in aggro generation to continue from there.<br>
<br>
And Graal, while your groups may never have tried the PoS giants, my groups have.  And I die about half the time because the Clerics can't compensate for how hard the giants hit, even with slowed.  I would never want to face one of those things for more than a few split seconds unslowed, I'm already dying fairly regularly with them slowed.  Maybe it's just bad luck or bad Clerics, but it happens.<br>
<br>
