<br>
My wife ( 65 Monk 7 k hp raidbuffed ) said that she can only bring out all of her damage without looking for aggro when a hybrid is tanking. With warriors she has to have a look at her aggro what means she is loosing damage.<br>
<br>
So were speaking about exp grinding.<br>
<br>
The normal exp group has<br>
one Tank<br>
one Healer<br>
one Slower<br>
3 Damagedealer<br>
<br>
So when a Warrior is tanking he maybe makes a fluffy of damage more than that tanking hybrid.<br>
1. the Cleric needs more mana for healing per fight<br>
2. the Slower has to control his aggro more .. means slow later ...<br>
3. the Damagedealers have to controll their aggro means lower their Damageoutput.<br>
<br>
Summary .. More healmana less groupdps .<br>
<br>
So when the Hybrid is tanking<br>
1. the cleric needs less mana for healing ( maybe now he can nuke once in 2 fights)<br>
2. the Slower can slow early .. ( maybe he can Dot the mob now )<br>
3. the Damagedealers can dish out more damage <br>
Summary ... Less healmana more groupdps<br>
<br>
More groupdps = faster kills = more mobs to kill in the same time = more EXP = thats why groups are exp grinding.<br>
<br>
And there is the point where the problem starts. Now ppl. see that they can make more exp in time with an hybrid as a tank. Now ppl. see that a hybrid as a tank is less risky than a warrior.<br>
<br>
Hm less risks more exp or more risk less exp.<br>
<br>
Which choice ?<br>
<br>
Sure the ppl. also take a warrior, but only when he is <br>
1. a friend<br>
2. a guildmember<br>
3. well named<br>
4. the only tank around.<br>
5. the traditional tank.<br>
<br>
But never they choose a warrior now cause he is the best for that tanking job.<br>
<br>
Man as a 55 th warrior in Sebi in March 2001 I had never the problems finding a group as now as 65 warrior with 1500 buffed AC and around 6.7k hp clericgroupbuffed with around 80 AAs.<br>
