Crusader of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 869<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 10:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: more sweet info to add :)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Did you get quest pieces from the giants? More importantly, did you have a chance at getting quest pieces from the giants?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Personally, I got my quest pieces when my guild took a couple of groups into PoS regularly specifically to get quest pieces.  Two groups have a much better chance of succeeding than one.<br>
<br>
Could I have gotten them without the guild help with one very solid group?  Yes, probably.   It would have entailed some willingness to bite it a number of times though, in all likelihood.<br>
<br>
And again, this is one case.  It's more of a mini-raid than it is an experience group scenario.  It's certainly not something that people who are looking to grind out the greatest amount of experience in the shortest period of time are going to want to do.  It's a quest.  Nor is it all that common a scenario.<br>
