</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A> at: 3/18/03 10:53:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khumak>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 267<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 11:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: more sweet info to add :)</span><hr size=1> The whole time your taunts argument is stupid.  What warrior gets to 65 without knowing when to taunt?  If taunt worked a significant percentage of the time then timing your taunt would make a big difference.  When it works 20% of the time then timing your taunt means that you'll get aggro anywhere from right when you want it to about 30 seconds after you needed it.  <br>
<br>
I never taunt if I have aggro, I save it until I lose aggro.  If I fail 2 or 3 taunts in a row I use AE taunt.  Once AE taunt has been used if I fail 2 or 3 taunts in a row my only option is /shield.  It's not all doom and gloom.  Most of the time I DO get aggro within a few seconds due to either a successful taunt or an EB proc.  <br>
<br>
The arguement still stands that knights are more efficient tanks because of the huge importance of aggro control in PoP.  Our lack of aggro control used to be justified by vastly superior tanking ability.  That vastly superior tanking ability has shrunk to almost nothing unless we use defensive.  Because of that our lack of aggro control is no longer justified.<br>
<br>
Can any knight say they would honestly give up all their spells plus LoH/HT for a 20% melee DPS boost, an extra 700 hps, a 1.5% avoidance boost, and defensive?  Hell, let's make it even easier.  How many would agree to changing the aggro on all their spells to 0 in exchange for the above boost?  Not many I'd wager. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=472195">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
