<br>
Like I said to Glatius earlier: exaggerate much?<br>
<br>
EDIT: and just to show how pathetic this whole argument is...I have played a handful of times in the past 5 months, and I have a ready made group waiting for me if I do decide to log in. The only reason I have played the few times I have is because my wife has whined that her group needed a tank and/or she informed me that there was someone on that I hadn't talked to in a long time. I have absolutely nothing to gain from this argument either way. It won't affect my chances of getting a group (which are, and will remain 100%), it won't affect my ability to act as tank for the groups my wife needs me to tank for. It MIGHT affect the ability of other knights to get a group. It MIGHT affect the overall health of the game. <br>
<br>
The fact that I'm bored at work and making these posts isn't a strong indication of my sanity, but oh well. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Crusader of Brell</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graalthedorf>Graal the Dorf</A> at: 3/18/03 11:38:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ninaor@thesteelwarrior>Ninaor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/03 11:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   one more thing...</span><hr size=1> I still personally think the hardest hit to warriors came with the recent revamp of 2h damage bonuses.  Up until that point knights were a joke when it came to DPS.  I mean 2h slashing and blunt just could not come close to keeping pace with two 1h slashers.  What did this mean?  More agro from constantly attacking the mob plus more agro from the increased DPS.<br>
<br>
And if a pally or SK switched to 1hander + shield ?  Well, even worse DPS.<br>
<br>
So let me ask you all this - if the pallies and SK's of today had to deal with the CRAPPY DPS of the old 2hander bonuses do you guys think they would be able to hold agro as well?  Also, would they be as desirable in groups ?  Would they EVER even be CONSIDERED for trials ?<br>
<br>
When 2h slashing was made DPS king, nothing was changed to avert the issue of taunting.  Now we have to either proc consistantly (which is theoretically impossible) OR we have to use a windblade like every knight in EQ.  When we use the Windblade we are attacking very slowly which means less attention from the mob based on how many times you attack it per second.  Additionally, we are now doing marginally higher DPS than the knight and therefore it is simple for him/her to draw agro with a high agro spell.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think when 2h damage bonuses were raised ridiculously high that was when the problems REALLY started for the warriors in the area of taunt and desirability.<br>
<br>
I'm sure this has probably been said on these boards many times in the past but I only recently (about a month ago) found these boards and haven't had a chance to look back.  Also, it has not been mentioned in this particular thread yet so I thought I would bring it up and see if all you warriors and hybrids would agree.<br>
<br>
~Ninaor<br>
